    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It's a `clique` network. That uses the `miner `field for something else. You can retrieve various information with `clique.getSnaphot(block_number)`. The `recents` field will contain the miners who signed the last few blocks.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, you can retrieve the RLP encoded header of a block and recover the signature from that (then it doesn't even need to be a block know to the node): `clique.getSigner(debug.getHeaderRlp(block_number))`",
